First, we notice that triangles $AXY$ and $BXZ$ are congruent.  Therefore, triangle $ABX$ has the same area as triangle $AYZ$.  Since $XC$ is an altitude of triangle $AYZ$ and $XC = XC$, triangle $CXY$ has the same area as triangle $CYZ$.  The shaded region is the difference between the area of triangle $ABC$ and the area of triangle $CXY$. Since $AB = \frac{XY}{2}$ and $XC = \frac{YZ}{2},$ the ratio of the area of triangle $ABC$ to the area of triangle $CXY$ is $\frac{AB}{XC} = \frac{XY}{2\cdot YZ},$ which equals $\frac{1}{4}$ since $AB = \frac{1}{2}\cdot XY$.  So the area of the shaded region is $\left(1-\frac{1}{4}\right)8 = \boxed{6}$ square inches. [asy]
